153- 22. Die matre. This is the reading os the best and the greater 56 number ot' Mss, not Dia. Cicero certainly did not find the Latin name of an agrarian deity in the writings of the Greek theologi whom he here fol- lows. Serv. note on Aen. 153. 23. Valentis. Cicero apparently gives this as the translation of the Greek name Ἰσχυς. According to the fable he was an Arcadian hero, who won the favor of the Thessalian Coronis, which Apollo had enjoyed before him. But Ischys is nowhere else mentioned as the father of Tropho- nius.
